File: The ban on cigarettes continues under level 3. JOHANNESBURG - Some hope for cigarette smokers. The legal challenge against a high court ruling, upholding of the ban on cigarette sales, will be heard on 15 July. The Fair Trade Independent Tobacco Association (Fita) has been granted leave to appeal the decision. It will go head-to-head with Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs ministry via Zoom. Tobacco ban: Fita files application for leave to appeal Government banned the sale of tobacco products when the country went into lockdown in March. Last month, the High Court in Pretoria ruled against Fita. The court said a product's addictive properties do not mean it can be deemed essential during the lockdown. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.